io.github.goodees.ese.core.sync

Class SyncEntity

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.goodees.ese.core.EventSourcedEntity
      • io.github.goodees.ese.core.sync.SyncEntity

  • public abstract class SyncEntity
extends EventSourcedEntity
    Event sourced entity that executes the request in synchronous manner. The programming model is seemingly easier, but does not conceptually separate event handling from side effects.

    This class requires its runtime to extends from SyncEventSourcingRuntime.

    Emitting events can be done by using methods persistAndUpdate(Event), persistAllAndUpdate(Event...), persistAllAndUpdate(Collection). Should these methods throw an exception the processing should not continue.

    See Also:
    AsyncEntity, SyncEventSourcingRuntime

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        protected abstract <R extends Request<RS>,RS> RS execute(R request)
                                                  throws Exception
        Execute the request. This model gives no direct limitations on how a request should be handled, however, it needs to be carefully designed in following blocks:
        1. Validation (not changing state of entity, or the system)
        2. Persisting events. When EventStoreException is thrown, it must be rethrown immediately.
        3. EventSourcedEntity.updateState(Event) will be called for every produced event after persistAndUpdate succeeds
        4. Performing side effects.
        5. If side effects fail, and are necessary for transition to new state, emitting compensating events.
        6. EventSourcedEntity.performPostInvocationActions(List, Throwable) is called by the runtime with events produced and optionally thrown exception
        Type Parameters:
        R - type of request
        RS - type of response
        Parameters:
        request - request to execute
        Returns:
        the response
        Throws:
        Exception - when response doesn't complete successfully
